Package com.sun.media.jsdt.http

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    JSDTSocketInfo
    JSDTSocketInfo is an interface that extensions of the java.net.Socket class may use to provide more information on its capabilities.
    ServletHandler.CommandHandler
    CommandHandler is the abstraction for an object that handles a particular supported command (for example the "forward" command "forwards" call information to a remote server on the local machine).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ByteArrayProxy
    JSDT Byte Array client-side proxy class.
    ByteArrayServer
    JSDT Byte Array Server-side class.
    CGIHandler
    The CGIHandler class contains methods for executing as a CGI program.
    ChannelProxy
    JSDT Session client-side proxy class.
    ChannelServer
    JSDT Channel Server-side class.
    DataReceivedMessage
    JSDT Channel client-side data received message class.
    DataReceivedQueue
    The queue of client-side data received messages.
    DataReceivedThread
    JSDT Channel client-side data received thread class.
    httpClient
    JSDT HTTP Client class.
    httpSession
    JSDT HTTP Session class.
    JSDTMasterSocketFactory
    JSDTMasterSocketFactory attempts to create a socket connection to the specified host using successively less efficient mechanisms until one succeeds.
    NamingProxy
    JSDT Naming proxy class (HTTP implementation).
    PingThread
    JSDT Session Proxy "ping for message" thread class.
    Registry
    JSDT Registry class (HTTP implementation).
    RegistryPingThread
    JSDT Naming Proxy "ping registry for messages" thread class.
    ServletHandler
    JSDT HTTP servlet handler class.
    ServletHandler.ServletForwardCommand
    Class that has an execute command to forward request body to local port on the server and send server reponse back to client.
    ServletHandler.ServletGethostnameCommand
    Class that has an execute method to return the host name of the server as the response body.
    ServletHandler.ServletPingCommand
    Class that has an execute method to return an OK status to indicate that connection was successful.
    ServletHandler.ServletTryHostnameCommand
    Class that has an execute method to return a human readable message describing which host name is available to local Java VMs.
    TCPSocketFactory
    TCPSocketFactory creates a direct socket connection to the specified port on the specified host.
    TokenProxy
    JSDT Token client-side proxy class.
    TokenServer
    JSDT Token Server-side class.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ServletHandler.ServletClientException
    ServletClientException is thrown when an error is detected in a client's request.
    ServletHandler.ServletServerException
    ServletServerException is thrown when an error occurs here on the server.
